1.translation: You will jump over the log.

5.translation: OK , I will/can jump that one.

notes: example - response to basic question (What is your name?)

15.translation: Who is that man? (What is that man called, e.g. accusative in S13 this document.)

18.translation: OK, I throw away this message stick.

20.translation: They are sending us a message stick.

21.translation: I think we will look for your boomerang.

22.translation: I will look for his boomerang.

23.translation: I looked, I couldn't find his boomerang.
23.full_text: wankinga barninyi nganyi wankinga nhungka bakarranyianga

24.translation: That group of women are having a fight.

25.translation: The day before yesterday the women all fought.

26.translation: Tomorrow the women will all fight (together).

27.translation: This fire is burning. I smell smoke.
27.full_text: wiyiani nhaniguru marrigala/ dhupuanha ngathu wupigala

28.translation: The woman is scolding this child.

29.translation: Cover up this kangaroo with ashes.

30.translation: OK, I will cover this meat.

33.translation: That man is telling a lie.

37.translation: Put (it) on the ground over there.

38.translation: OK, I put (it) over there on the ground.

40.translation: OK, I will hold (it) for you.

41.translation: Show me that boomerang, I want to see it.
41.full_text: dumpa nganha nhanhaguru bakarranyinha/ ngathu nadyarra

42.translation: I will not show you, I haven't finished (it) yet.
42.full_text: walya ngathu inha dumparra/ walya gadha ngathu mulpagala

43.translation: I think the two of us will hide over there.

44.translation: Here look out quick for kangaroos.

46.translation: A stick fell in the road. (A stick has fallen on the road.) The two of us will drag it away I think.
46.full_text: makurra nhaniguru buligaliani gurrgalanga wirlidhirra bari ngalingu

47.translation: Look out one might fall on you.

49.translation: This stick is rotten. I think it will fall soon. (This stick is rotten so I think it will fall.)
49.full_text: makurrani nhaniyi garlgugarlgunhani/ guntutyirri nhani bari bulirra

51.translation: Look out, it might bite you.

53.translation: Hey don't go away, I want to see you.
53.full_text: gari walya yanhtha/ nadyarra ngathu inha

54.translation: Hey, tell that one I want to see him.
54.full_text: gari bura nhanhaguru nadyarra ngathu nhanha

57.translation: Hey you two, tell (him) I want to see him.
57.full_text: gala bula bura nadyarra ngathu nhanha

58.translation: OK, I told him, he will wait, you will see him.
58.full_text: murra ngathu buranga nhanha/ gulharra nhani/ yundru nadyarra nhanha

60.translation: You will follow me. (Repeated twice in original corpus.)

62.translation: I cannot carry this. It is big.
62.full_text: walya ngathu nhanhaguru gangalangu/ gumiani nhaniguru

63.translation: Yes I will help you. The two of us will carry this one.
63.full_text: ga ngathu inha walibarra/ ngalingu barrkululu ganggarra nhanhaguru
